Similarly:

```csharp
var fv = FileVersionInfo.GetVersionInfo(@"C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio\2019\IntPreview\MSBuild\Current\Bin\MSBuild.exe");
Console.WriteLine($"ProductVersion: {fv.ProductVersion}");
Console.WriteLine($"ProductMajorPart: {fv.ProductMajorPart}");
Console.WriteLine($"ProductMinorPart: {fv.ProductMinorPart}");
Console.WriteLine($"ProductBuildPart: {fv.ProductBuildPart}");
Console.WriteLine($"ProductPrivatePart: {fv.ProductPrivatePart}");
```
produces

```
ProductVersion: 16.2.0-preview.19264.2+c3389964cd55d027344584a70cc8f3f9e0fb348b
ProductMajorPart: 0
ProductMinorPart: 0
ProductBuildPart: 0
ProductPrivatePart: 0
```

@KalleOlaviNiemitalo I was chasing the same thing:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3347530/57941616-462ed000-7884-11e9-844a-9c22e1d3f997.png)

The recent change that caused this is https://github.com/microsoft/msbuild/pull/4318; the two issues you looked at were about different versions.
